# IceSugar 40 (iCE40UP5K-SG48) pin constraints for Open8 soft core demo
#
# VISIBLE OUTPUT ON A STOCK iCESUGAR BOARD (no extra hardware):
#   The board has a single onboard RGB LED driven by the iCE40UP5K hard IP
#   (SB_RGBA_DRV primitive in boards/icesugar40/top.v). This design drives that
#   RGB LED directly from the 8-bit port_out value produced by the Open8 core.
#
#   - When the blink example writes 0x00 to port 0, the RGB LED turns ON (bright).
#   - When it writes 0xFF, the RGB LED turns OFF.
#   The blink.s has a ~0.35 s half-period delay (three nested loops) so you should
#   see a slow, clear blink on the small RGB LED near the center/USB side of the board.
#
#   IMPORTANT:
#   * The RGB pins are SPECIAL. They are claimed automatically by the SB_RGBA_DRV
#     primitive. DO NOT add any "set_io LED_R ...", "set_io LED_G ...", or
#     "set_io LED_B ..." lines in this file. If you do, nextpnr will error.
#   * Look at the actual RGB LED on the board after programming, not random FPGA pins.
#
# The led0..led7 signals below are for people who connect an external 8-LED PMOD
# board or discrete LEDs to the PMOD headers. Those pins are just regular user IO.
# The numbers below are still somewhat guessed — adjust to your actual PMOD wiring
# if you add a LED board. On many PMOD LED boards the LEDs are active-low.
#
# Reset button (KEY / DIP switch on iCESugar): active-low when pressed.
# We treat a low on the pin as an external reset request.
#
# References:
#   https://github.com/wuxx/icesugar/tree/master/schematic  (iCESugar-v1.5.pdf etc.)
#   https://github.com/wuxx/icesugar/tree/master/src/basic/verilog/common/io.pcf
#   https://github.com/wuxx/icesugar/tree/master/src/basic/verilog/hard_rgb

# --- Clock input ---
# Match the style used in the reference icesugar40-example designs
# (e.g. src/basic/verilog/leds/leds.v declares "input clk" at the top level).
# Pin 35 is the conventional clock pin on iCESugar / many iCE40UP5K boards
# (see common/io.pcf and multiple *.pcf files in the icesugar40-example repo).
set_io clk 35

# --- Reset button (input, active low when pressed) ---
set_io rst_btn 10

# --- 8 optional LED outputs for PMOD LED board or external LEDs ---
# These follow the mapping from the reference pmod_leds/led.pcf (when clk is on 35).
# The top.v drives them with the inverted port value (~port_out) because
# many PMOD LED boards light when the pin is low (active-low LEDs).
# If you use different wiring or active-high LEDs, adjust the numbers or the
# polarity in the 8 assign statements in top.v.
set_io led0 45
set_io led1 43
set_io led2 38
set_io led3 36
set_io led4 46
set_io led5 44
set_io led6 42
set_io led7 37

# --- If you have UART / other I/O, add them here and wire in top.v ---
# set_io uart_tx  ...
# set_io uart_rx  ...

# Notes:
# - Package: sg48 (QFN-48)
# - Device: iCE40UP5K
# - clk is on pin 35 (standard for most icesugar40-example designs, see leds.v style).
# - led0-7 use the pmod_leds mapping (safe when clk=35). These are optional.
# - NO set_io lines for the onboard RGB LED (LED_R / LED_G / LED_B).
#   The SB_RGBA_DRV primitive in top.v owns those dedicated package pins.
# - After editing, re-run: make EXAMPLE=blink BOARD=icesugar40 fpga-clean bitstream prog
# - Power-cycle the board after the iCELink copy completes.
#
# The Makefile passes --pcf-allow-unconstrained to nextpnr because the RGB pins
# (LED_R/G/B) are intentionally left unconstrained — they are claimed by the
# SB_RGBA_DRV primitive in top.v and must not have set_io lines here.